## Graceful Shutdown

Every deployed process should handle termination signals cleanly:

```
On SIGTERM / SIGINT:
  1. Stop accepting new connections
  2. Finish in-flight requests (with a timeout - [DEFAULT] 30 seconds)
  3. Close database connections, flush logs
  4. Exit with code 0
```

- Never kill processes abruptly in production - always allow drain time
- Set Docker `STOPSIGNAL SIGTERM` and `stop_grace_period` to match your drain timeout
- Listen for termination signals in your application and trigger a clean shutdown (language/framework-specific)
- Log the shutdown event at INFO level so you can verify clean shutdowns in production

