## Static SPA + API Deploy (When Applicable)

When frontends are **static SPAs** (Vite, CRA, etc.) and the API runs on compute:

```
Browser  ->  CloudFront / CDN  ->  S3 bucket (HTML/JS/CSS)
Browser  ->  api.example.com   ->  EC2 / container (Express, etc.)
Workers  ->  (no public URL)   ->  EC2 / container (private subnet)
```

**Frontend (S3 + CloudFront):**

- Private S3 bucket; CloudFront Origin Access Control (OAC) - no public bucket ACLs.
- `index.html` cache policy: short TTL or invalidation on deploy; hashed assets: long cache.
- TLS via ACM on CloudFront; redirect HTTP to HTTPS.
- Separate distribution per app when origins differ (trader app vs admin app).

**API + workers:**

- API behind ALB or nginx with TLS.
- Workers: no public IP; outbound-only to vendors + DB/Redis.

**Selective deploy script** - support deploying components independently:

```
pnpm deploy --prod --website     # build SPA -> S3 sync -> CloudFront invalidation
pnpm deploy --prod --admin       # same for admin bucket
pnpm deploy --prod --server      # API only
pnpm deploy --prod --workers     # all worker packages
pnpm deploy --prod               # everything
```

CI may mirror this with separate workflows per artifact or one script with flags - document which in `docs/setup.md`.

**Rules:**

- Build every deployable app in CI before merge (see CI/CD § Rules).
- Frontends never embed API keys - only public API base URL and IdP client IDs.
- Smoke test API health + one critical SPA route after each prod deploy.

