## Health Checks

IF your service is deployed, expose:

```
GET /health
  -> 200: { "status": "healthy", "timestamp": "..." }
  -> 503: { "status": "unhealthy", "checks": { ... } }

Checks (include those relevant to your project):
  - Database connectivity
  - Cache connectivity (if applicable)
  - Disk space
  - Memory usage
  - Critical external service connectivity
```

**Rules:**
- Health endpoint does NOT require authentication
- Health checks are lightweight (don't run expensive queries)
- Load balancer polls health endpoint (unhealthy -> remove from rotation)
- Kubernetes readiness/liveness probes point to health endpoint

